{"questionId":"27772","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, by applying l’Hôpital’s rule, show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to differentiate both the numerator and the denominator&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfenced><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder></mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>.&nbsp;This form can be used in subsequent work.</p>\n<p><br>(l’Hôpital’s rule applies again since)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>0</mn><mn>0</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong>&nbsp;</em>if&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder></math>&nbsp;is not referred to or stated.&nbsp;Subsequent marks are independent of this <em><strong>R</strong></em> mark.</p>\n<p><br>attempts to differentiate both the numerator and the denominator&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo>